nodes.documentation:
@notice Propose transition object and vote message from seal
        for the open kernel.
     * @dev Function requires:
         - core is opened
         - the given kernel hash matches to the opened kernel hash in core
         - origin observation is not 0
         - dynasty is strictly greater than committed dynasty
         - accumulated gas is strictly greater than committed
           accumulated gas
         - committee lock (transition root hash) is not 0
         - source blockhash is not 0
         - target blockhash is not 0
         - source block number is strictly greater than committed
           block number
         - source block number is a checkpoint
         - target block number is +1 epoch of the source block number
         - a proposal matching with the input parameters does
           not exist in the core
     * @param _kernelHash Kernel hash of a proposed metablock.
@param _originObservation Origin observation of a proposed metablock.
@param _dynasty Dynasty of a proposed metablock.
@param _accumulatedGas Accumulated gas in a proposed metablock.
@param _committeeLock Committee lock (transition root hash) of a proposed
                      metablock.
@param _source Source blockhash of a vote message for a proposed metablock.
@param _target Target blockhash of a vote message for a proposed metablock.
@param _sourceBlockNumber Source block number of a vote message for a
                          proposed metablock.
@param _targetBlockNumber Target block number of a vote message for a
                          proposed metablock.
     * @return proposal_ Returns a proposal based on input parameters.

@notice Registers a validator's vote for the given proposal.
        If the validator has already registered a vote for currently
        opened kernel height, it gets updated (only if dynasty number
        of the new vote is higher then the previous one).
     * @dev Function requires:
         - core is in precommitment window
         - proposal is not 0
         - if core has precommitted, the given proposal matches with it
         - proposal exists at open kernel height
         - validator active in this core
         - validator should not be slashed in reputation contract
         - validator has not already cast the same vote
         - vote gets updated only if the new vote is at higher dynasty

forwardValidatorSetCount(uint256).details: Function requires:         - height is less than active height

params._height: Height for which to return the forward validator set count.

params._gasTarget: The gas target for this metablock
params._parent: The hash of this block's parent.
params._updatedReputation: The array of reputation that corresponds to                       the updated validators.
params._updatedValidators: The array of addresses of the updated validators.

params._accumulatedGas: Accumulated gas in a provided metablock.
params._committeeLock: Committee lock (transition root hash) of a provided                      metablock.
params._kernelHash: Kernel hash of a provided metablock.
params._originObservation: Origin observation of a provided metablock.
params._source: Source blockhash of a vote message for a               provided metablock.
params._sourceBlockNumber: Source block number of a vote message for a                          provided metablock.
params._target: Target blockhash of a vote message for a               provided metablock.
params._targetBlockNumber: Target block number of a vote message for a                          provided metablock.

join(address).details: Function requires:         - only consensus can call         - core is in a running state         - validators' join limit for the core has not been reached         - maximum number of validators to join in a single metablock           has not been reached         - given validator address is not 0         - validator has not joined

params._validator: Address of a validator to join.

join(address).return: beginHeight_ Begin height of the validator

joinBeforeOpen(address).details: Function requires:         - only consensus can call         - core is created state and not open         - a validator's address is not null         - a validator has not already joined
joinBeforeOpen(address).return: validatorCount_ The total count of validators.minValidatorCount_ Minimum validator count required set by consensus.beginHeight_ Begin height of validator.

logout(address).details: Function requires:         - only consensus can call         - core is in a running state         - validators' minimum limit has not been reached         - maximum number of validators to logout in a single metablock           has not been reached         - given validator address is not 0         - validator has joined

params._validator: An address of the validator to logout.

openMetablock(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Function requires:         - core has precommitted         - only consensus can call         - input parameters match to an open metablock

params._committedAccumulatedGas: Accumulated gas in an open metablock.
params._committedSourceBlockNumber: Source block number of a vote message                                   for an open metablock.
params._deltaGasTarget: Gas target delta for a new metablock.

proposeMetablock(bytes32,bytes32,uint256.details: Function requires:         - core is opened         - the given kernel hash matches to the opened kernel hash in core         - origin observation is not 0         - dynasty is strictly greater than committed dynasty         - accumulated gas is strictly greater than committed           accumulated gas         - committee lock (transition root hash) is not 0         - source blockhash is not 0         - target blockhash is not 0         - source block number is strictly greater than committed           block number         - source block number is a checkpoint         - target block number is +1 epoch of the source block number         - a proposal matching with the input parameters does           not exist in the core

params._accumulatedGas: Accumulated gas in a proposed metablock.
params._committeeLock: Committee lock (transition root hash) of a proposed                      metablock.
params._kernelHash: Kernel hash of a proposed metablock.
params._originObservation: Origin observation of a proposed metablock.
params._source: Source blockhash of a vote message for a proposed metablock.
params._sourceBlockNumber: Source block number of a vote message for a                          proposed metablock.
params._target: Target blockhash of a vote message for a proposed metablock.
params._targetBlockNumber: Target block number of a vote message for a                          proposed metablock.

proposeMetablock(bytes32,bytes32,uint256.return: proposal_ Returns a proposal based on input parameters.

registerVote(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,uin.details: Function requires:         - core is in precommitment window         - proposal is not 0         - if core has precommitted, the given proposal matches with it         - proposal exists at open kernel height         - validator active in this core         - validator should not be slashed in reputation contract         - validator has not already cast the same vote         - vote gets updated only if the new vote is at higher dynasty

removeVote(address).details: Function requires:         - only consensus can call         - core is in running state

params._validator: Address of a validator to remove a vote.

validatorSetCount(uint256).details: Function requires:         - height is less than active height

params._height: Height for which to return the validator set count.

forwardValidatorSetCount(uint256).notice: returns the forward validator set count for heights up to active height, but not included.

getOpenKernel().notice: It returns open kernel hash and height.

hashKernel(uint256,bytes32,address[],uin.notice: Takes the parameters of a kernel object and returns the        typed hash of it.

hashMetablock(bytes32,bytes32,uint256,ui.notice: Hashes given parameters of a metablock.

inForwardValidatorSet(address,uint256).notice: Checks if validator is in forward validator set or not.

inValidatorSet(address,uint256).notice: Checks if validator is in validator set or not.

isValidator(address).notice: Validator is active if it is validator set at open kernel height.

joinBeforeOpen(address).notice: Joins a validator before core is opened.        Once the minimum number of validators has joined, core is opened,        with the metablock parameters specified in the constructor.

openMetablock(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Opens a new metablock if a proposal is precommitted.

proposeMetablock(bytes32,bytes32,uint256.notice: Propose transition object and vote message from seal        for the open kernel.

registerVote(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,uin.notice: Registers a validator's vote for the given proposal.        If the validator has already registered a vote for currently        opened kernel height, it gets updated (only if dynasty number        of the new vote is higher then the previous one).

removeVote(address).notice: Remove vote can be called by consensus when a validator        is slashed, to retro-actively remove the vote from the        current open metablock.

validatorSetCount(uint256).notice: returns the validator set count for heights up to active height, but not included.
